      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "MAYWYNS MIGHTY MAC (3) has been a bit hot and cold and that continued last start when he finished third, beaten 4.5 metres, in a nice return to form at Newcastle over 1609m. No excuses from this advantageous draw. Meets some better types this time but he has the ability to play a significant role. THREE RIVERS NZ (6) hasn't had a lot go to plan since winning at this circuit and distance back in February. This looks a suitable assignment. LACHIES IDEAL (7) did a good job to finish in the minor placings two runs back then his luck changed last time when he broke and finished a long way back in eighth over 1609m at this track. Won't spend a penny from this draw but luck may play a role on the bell lap. Only needs to get things right to be in contention. IM LORD TOMMY (2) is worth some thought after his last-start fifth over 1609m at this track.",
